# LaTeX — PEF papers

## Language

British English: recognised, behaviour, rigour, optimisation, generalised.

## Maths

- Greek in math mode: `$\eta$`, `$\kappa$`, `$\rho$`, `$\psi$`, `$\tau$` — not Unicode
- Canonical form: `\eta = \cosh\tau/(\cosh\tau - \rho)` with `\tau=\tfrac{1}{2}\log\kappa`
- Numbered equations with labels; cross-ref empirical paper for data, not re-derive KPI tables here

## Structure

- `sections/numerical_validation.tex` ↔ files in `validation_inputs/` — cite pipeline CSV columns, do not invent values

## Tone

Theory-first; empirical validation is imported numerics, not new six-domain ML claims.

